review_blob: A very tasty, rich flavor. Nice head, nice aroma. Overall good, not great, but very good.
I like hefewizens, and was hesitant to try out the "american" version... I was pleasantly surprised. Very nice beer, its going into the rotation.
Not quite there in flavor, aroma or appearance. Not bad, but you can definitely do better.
It has a terrific appearance. A very complex taste, it says its brewed with spice, and you can actually taste it. Very satisfying beer.
Very nice color, and OK aroma. First one went down smoothly, the second one did not fare as well. Middle of the pack.
beer_name: Tap Room No. 21 Moes Backroom Amber Ale

review_blob: Great aroma, you can actually smell the apricots. It has a nice smooth finish, they really did a nice job of balancing the flavors so that the fruit tones do not stand out too strongly.
I found it a bit flat, but not at all bad. It does have tasty caramel flavor, but I guess my tastebuds were expecting more.
A fantastic fruity beer. Its a literal blast of flavor. This is a favorite of my wife as she says she cant really tell that she is drinking alcohol. Very very good.
Dark roasty beer, it has a very full-taste not unlike banana bread. I thought it was a bit heavy, but overall very good.
The lowest denominator in beer. I only have it when there is nothing else. Literally. Id rather have anything else.
I feel lucky to find this beer at my local Club where mostly macro-bre fare is served. It has a nice look to it and it tastes great.
Regular Tecate is bad enough, the "Light" version is just brutal. Watery, metalic taste, whats to like?
Terrible corn-like taste. Tastes watered down, with hints of metal. Not good at all.
A traditional mexican pale lager. It is considered a little upscale, compared to other local mexican beers. It does have a slight caramel aroma and a slight bitter taste.
Barely a beer. Its OK if youre at the beach and there is nothing else, but overall it pretty lame. The clear bottle does not help.

beer_brewer_name: Leinenkugel Brewing Company (Tenth & Blake Beer Co.)
review_blob: A verey refreshing beer no doubt. Ideal for a hot day outside. The lemonade flavor really stands out. If yourre not into lemonade-tasting beer, this is not for you.

I did not expect to like it, but I did. Its aroma may be off putting, but it actually tastes better that it smells. It has a fruity taste, but not so strong as to make you forget that what you are drinking is beer.

A nice, rich flavor. You could do a lot worse. This beer has strong distribution here in Texas, so you find it along the usual macro-bre fare, which is usually quite bad. And if that is the case, Shiner is the way to go.
Not my favorite. A very weak aroma. Its appereance is ok, its a clear golden beer, but it comes up short in flavor. A ver light bitter taste. Very very average.
The aroma is a toasty-nutty one. It has a pale brown appereance, almost cloudy. It has a very distinct flavor, not too bitter. Medium body.
Quite the little beer. A toasty aroma and a clear amber appereance. A beer with a medium bitter taste. It does have a nice and lively flavor to it.
In my opinion the best of the commercial mexican beers. It has a ligh caramel aroma, an lightly dark amber appereance, and a medium taste. A nice alternative to the usual fare.
It has a very weak aroma. Its a golden clear beer, with a very light bitter taste. Its ok for a hot summer day.

beer_brewer_name: Leinenkugel Brewing Company (Tenth & Blake Beer Co.)
review_blob: A heady beer with a strong floral fruity aroma. It looks like it has berries, it has a purple hazy, look. This is a heavily sweet beer, but it does pack quite a punch.
A complex beer. Its appearance was golden, pale, and  a bit hazy. A full body with a lively taste and a long finish. Enjoyed it quite a bit, On Tap!
This is a beer that has a very full, fruity flavor, without being overly sweet. The aroma is quite noticeable, but in a good way. Has been a personal favorite for quite a while now.
